Spicing things up for the weekend! Spicy Jalapeño Watermelon Margaritas 🍹🍉
Also just in time for #nationaltequiladay July24th 

Spicy Watermelon Jalapeno Margaritas
Makes 4 Servings

4 cups cubed seedless watermelon
1 tablespoons sugar (optional)
4 jalapenos, with seeds and membranes, roughly chopped
2 limes, juiced
8 ounces clear tequila

Place the watermelon( and sugar, if using) in a blender and process until smooth, keep chilled in a pitcher in the refrigerator until ready to use. 
Place jalapeno in a blender with 2/3 cup water and puree until very smooth. Strain through a mesh sieve, add lime juice and keep chilled.

When ready to serve, fill a tall glass to the top with ice, pour 2 ounces tequila in each tall glass then add watermelon juice filling 3/4 of the way, about 1/2 cup then top with jalapeno juice.
